'''Almir Izmailovich Kayumov''' ({{lang-ru|<U+0410><U+043B><U+044C><U+043C><U+0438><U+0440> <U+0418><U+0437><U+043C><U+0430><U+0439><U+043B><U+043E><U+0432><U+0438><U+0447> <U+041A><U+0430><U+044E><U+043C><U+043E><U+0432>}}; born December 30, 1964) is a Russian football referee and a former [[USSR|Soviet]] and [[Russia]]n football player who played defense.

His previous clubs were [[FC Neftekhimik Nizhnekamsk]], [[FC Lada Togliatti]], [[FC Spartak Moscow|Spartak Moscow]], [[Rotor Volgograd]], [[SKA Rostov-on-Don]], [[Daewoo Royals]] in [[South Korea]], and [[Kuopion Palloseura]] in [[Finland]].

He played 6 games in the [[UEFA Cup 1986<U+2013>87]] for [[FC Spartak Moscow]].

It was reported that on November 9, 2009 he tried to commit suicide by jumping out of his apartment window; police negotiators talked him down, however, and he was brought to a psychiatric hospital.<ref name="suicide">{{Cite news | last = Wilson   | first = Jonathan   | title = Russian referee attempts suicide   | pages =    | newspaper = The Independent   | location = London   | date = 13 November 2009   | url = http://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/european/russian-referee-attempts-suicide-1819805.html | accessdate = <!-----13 November 2009----->}}</ref><ref name="russian suicide">[http://www.interfax.ru/sport/news.asp?id=109556&sw=%EA%E0%FE%EC%EE%E2&bd=11&bm=10&by=2009&ed=11&em=11&ey=2009&secid=0&mp=0&p=1 <U+0412> <U+041C><U+043E><U+0441><U+043A><U+0432><U+0435> <U+043F><U+044B><U+0442><U+0430><U+043B><U+0441><U+044F> <U+043F><U+043E><U+043A><U+043E><U+043D><U+0447><U+0438><U+0442><U+044C> <U+0436><U+0438><U+0437><U+043D><U+044C> <U+0441><U+0430><U+043C><U+043E><U+0443><U+0431><U+0438><U+0439><U+0441><U+0442><U+0432><U+043E><U+043C> <U+0444><U+0443><U+0442><U+0431><U+043E><U+043B><U+044C><U+043D><U+044B><U+0439> <U+0441><U+0443><U+0434><U+044C><U+044F> <U+041A><U+0430><U+044E><U+043C><U+043E><U+0432>]</ref> Kayumov denied this, stating that he had just an ordinary treatment.<ref>{{cite web|date=November 19, 2009|url=http://www.championat.ru/football/news-355331.html|title=<U+041A><U+0430><U+044E><U+043C><U+043E><U+0432>: <U+0432><U+0435><U+0440><U+0441><U+0438><U+044F> <U+043E> <U+043F><U+043E><U+043F><U+044B><U+0442><U+043A><U+0435> <U+0441><U+0430><U+043C><U+043E><U+0443><U+0431><U+0438><U+0439><U+0441><U+0442><U+0432><U+0430> <U+2014> <U+0431><U+0440><U+0435><U+0434>!|publisher=Championat.ru|lang=ru|accessdate=2009-11-29}}</ref>

==Honours==
* [[Soviet Top League]] champion: 1987.
* Soviet Top League runner-up: 1984, 1985.
* Soviet Top League bronze: 1986.
* [[Soviet Cup]] winner: 1992.

